"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFundic gland polyps\u003C/strong\u003E are the most common benign gastric polyps, comprising approximately 50% of all gastric polyps. They typically appear as multiple small lesions in the gastric body and fundus (Image 1). They are often associated with the long-term use of proton-pump inhibitors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyperplastic polyps\u003C/strong\u003E are the second most common type, usually occurring in the setting of chronic gastritis (Image 2).  \u003Cstrong\u003EStromal tumours\u003C/strong\u003E arise from the connective tissue of the stomach wall and are relatively rare (Image 3). \u003Cstrong\u003EAdenomatous polyps\u003C/strong\u003E account for only about 10% of gastric polyps but carry a higher risk of malignant transformation (Image 4).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInflammatory polyps\u003C/strong\u003E develop in response to mucosal injury and inflammation but are not the most common type (Image 5). \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fundic gland polyps are the most common benign gastric polyps, accounting for about 50% of all gastric polyps.","Fundic gland polyps are typically small, multiple, and located in the gastric body and fundus."],"references":["Arnold M, Abnet CC, Neale RE, Vignat J, Giovannucci EL, McGlynn KA, Bray F. Global Burden of 5 Major Types of Gastrointestinal Cancer. Gastroenterology. 2020 Jul;159(1):335-349.e15. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2020.02.068. Epub 2020 Apr 2. PMID: 32247694; PMCID: PMC8630546.","Goh PMY, Lenzi JE. Benign tumors of the duodenum and stomach. In: Holzheimer RG, Mannick JA, editors. Surgical Treatment: Evidence-Based and Problem-Oriented. Munich: Zuckschwerdt; 2001. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK6948/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of g